[{"location":"api/#API","page":"API","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"CurrentModule = SteadyWaves","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Pages = [\"api.md\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Modules = [SteadyWaves]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#SteadyWaves.SteadyWaves","page":"API","title":"SteadyWaves.SteadyWaves","text":"SteadyWaves is an implementation of Rienecker and Fenton (1981) Fourier Approximation Method to steady, periodic, nonlinear waves propagating in water of constant depth.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"api/#SteadyWaves.dispertion_relation","page":"API","title":"SteadyWaves.dispertion_relation","text":"dispertion_relation(d, ω, g=9.81, ϵ=10^-12)\n\nCalculate wavenumber k based on depth d, angular wave frequency ω and gravitational acceleration g for given accuracy ϵ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#SteadyWaves.f-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"API","title":"SteadyWaves.f","text":"f(du, u, p)\n\nDefine nonlinear system f(u) = 0 with parameters p.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SteadyWaves.fourier_approx-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"API","title":"SteadyWaves.fourier_approx","text":"fourier_approx(d, H, P; pc=1, cc=1, N=10, M=1, g=9.81)\n\nApproximate solution u of a steady wave of height H and length L propagating in water of depth d using Fourier Approximation Method.\n\n...\n\nArguments\n\nd: water depth (m)\nH: wave height (m)\nP: wave parameter - length L (m) or period T (s)\npc: parameter criterion; pc=1 - length (default), pc=2 - period\ncc: current criterion; cc=1 - Stokes (default), cc=2 - Euler\nN: number of solution eigenvalues, defaults to N=10\nM: number of height steps, defaults to M=1\ng: gravity acceleration (m/s^2), defaults to g=9.81\n\nOutput (nondimensional)\n\nu[1:N+1]: free surface elevation kη\nu[N+2:2N+1]: stream function coefficients B\nu[2N+2]: wave celerity c√(k/g)\nu[2N+3]: mean water depth kη̄\nu[2N+4]: volume flux due to waves q√(k³/g)\nu[2N+5]: Bernoulli constant rk/g\nu[2N+6]: mean flow velocity Ū√(k/g)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#SteadyWaves.init_conditions-NTuple{6, Any}","page":"API","title":"SteadyWaves.init_conditions","text":"init_conditions(d, H, P, pc, N, M)\n\nCalculate initial conditions u0 of a steady wave of height H and length L propagating in water of depth d using linear wave theory.\n\n...\n\nArguments\n\nd: water depth (m)\nH: wave height (m)\nP: wave parameter - length L (m) or period T (s)\npc: parameter criterion; pc=1 - length, pc=2 - period\nN: number of solution eigenvalues\nM: number of height steps\n\nOutput (nondimensional)\n\nu[1:N+1]: free surface elevation kη\nu[N+2:2N+1]: stream function coefficients B\nu[2N+2]: wave celerity c√(k/g)\nu[2N+3]: mean water depth kη̄\nu[2N+4]: volume flux due to waves q√(k³/g)\nu[2N+5]: Bernoulli constant rk/g\nu[2N+6]: mean flow velocity Ū√(k/g)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = SteadyWaves","category":"page"},{"location":"#SteadyWaves","page":"Home","title":"SteadyWaves","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for SteadyWaves. SteadyWaves is an implementation of Rienecker and Fenton (1981) Fourier Approximation Method to steady, periodic, nonlinear waves propagating in water of constant depth.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Install","page":"Home","title":"Install","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"pkg> add https://github.com/mcpaprota/SteadyWaves.jl","category":"page"}]
